In this article, President Barack Obama declares June 2014 as Great Outdoors Month in the United States. He highlights the importance of America's natural landscapes, which provide refuge, attract tourism, create jobs, and honor cultural heritage. The President emphasizes the need to protect these open spaces for future generations. He mentions the conservation efforts of past presidents and the responsibility of each citizen to continue their legacy. President Obama discusses the initiatives his administration has undertaken to increase access to public lands, engage young people and veterans in conservation efforts, and promote outdoor activities for children. He urges all Americans to explore the great outdoors and uphold the nation's legacy of conserving lands and waters.